<a href="javascript:card_browser(75)">Goblin Scimitar</a> x4    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Hello everyone,<br>
<br>
here are the bare bone basics of the deck.  Bid one.  This beats out the one bids and lets you get Aragorn right off the bat.  If they beat you in the bid then see what they are starting.  If they start the riddlemark than start Legolas and Eowyn, if they start another location than start with either Aragorn or something that will help you to the fullest (I lost a bid and my oppenent pulled the site one that pulls Legolas, so I got Arwen and Eowyn...like that) but pretty much, you are always going to want to start with Legolas, that ensures a double move to site three.<br>
<br>
  You are going to double move of course, picking off any little minions at site two and then taking on anything they got at three.  You don&#39;t need to worry about the Ford so you are sooooo safe!<br>
<br>
  Armor is a broken broken BROKEN card.  You can put on Eowyn, Eomer, Theoden, anyone you want!  It&#39;s amazing!  So put a Armor on Aragorn and Eowyn so you don&#39;t worry about Uruk-hai&#39;s.  This deck will eat up Uruks, what with the two Armors, the new Aragorn sword, and Orophin.  I played against two Uruk-Hai decks at the tournament and had no toubles with either.<br>
<br>
  People told me to use Isildur&#39;s bane, because I can take archery with it.  I explain this to them:  ATATR gives you six wounds!   SIX!  Plus, you have seven other comanions to suck up archery, PLUS on top of that even, the only archery decks you need to worry about now is Raider archers, and if you have the cards to make a Raider deck you will want to make a burden deck, simply because it&#39;ll work better and faster than archery, and I know there is that one Raider/archery player reading this getting a heart attack, so to that player I say I am dreadfully sorry, but your deck is poo.<br>
<br>
  This deck can either kill Frodo or move to nine, which I think makes the deck good.  This deck also stops your oppenent very well if you are double moving every turn.<br>
<br>
Another person said &quot;Wilson, what happens when you play against Gandalf and they Sleep?&quot;  I make sure I have the conditions I need on the table and nothing more.  You only need a Swarms, and a They are Coming.  And I stack two in the deck, so I have no worrys.  Another thing you might say is that the Armorys is very helpful, I say yes, they are helpful, helpful to keep my Goblins alive past Archery.  As soon as I play them I will sac them to Archery, I won&#39;t have them sitting on the table with Gandalf waiting to get discarded.  Sleep is during the Fellowship phase, so they need to stay on the table for more than one turn for them to sleep them.  Another thing is I didn&#39;t see one Gandalf all tournament, I only saw Rohan and big Fellowship.<br>
<br>
Moria is the best culture out there for one reason.  Rohan is very popular.  What the Rohan&#39;s do it make my minions exert and than they get strength bonus&#39; for my exerted minions.  Now, what better race than Moria to get around that.  The minions that will need to exert are big enough to still be able to whack them or at least live to the second round of fighting, aka the cave troll.<br>
<br>
One very last thing.  Once Bill the Pony hits the table, he will NEVER LEAVE!  HORRAY!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!<br>
<br>
